                "caption": "Figure 1:WIZARD: Weight-space Inference for Zero-shot Adaptation from Robotic Demonstration.(Left) Meta-Training.A repository of taskexpertsis built from LIBERO-Goal, -Object, and -10 datasets. For each task, a LoRA adapter (Δ​Wi\\Delta W^{i}) is trained while a multimodal encoder extracts a task embeddingziz^{i}from the instruction and visual demonstration. The meta-network learns to map embeddings to LoRA parameters by reconstructing the expert weights (zi→Δ​Wi~z^{i}\\rightarrow\\Delta\\tilde{W^{i}}).(Right) Zero-Shot Inference.Given a new task (e.g., from LIBERO-Spatial),WIZARDdirectly predicts the adaptation weightsΔ​W~new\\Delta\\tilde{W}^{\\text{new}}from the task embeddingznewz^{\\text{new}}, enabling zero-shot policy adaptation without gradient-based fine-tuning, even for unseen tasks.",
